The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Mumbai cops
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Mumbai cops
                            
	Mumbai, Dec. 23 (PTI): The names of the 14 policemen who died in the Mumbai terror attack have been recommended for Ashoka Chakra, Indias highest peacetime gallantry award.        
	Of the 14, one police- man worked for the railways while the rest were from Mumbai police. The list has been forwarded to the Union home ministry, Mumbai police commissioner Hasan Gafoor said.        
	Mumbai police have also recommended the names of 18 policemen who confronted the terrorists for the Presidents Police Medal.                                                                                                                                                                          
